column3:
Endgrain walnut rounds—heartwood chocolate to honeyed sapwood—are composed into a gentle “swell.” Natural voids are finished with black matte epoxy to unify the surface. The piece is then sealed in an oil-based finish with a micro-ceramic topcoat for tactile, long-wear protection.

  • Solid oak / walnut endgrain rounds, arranged by hand

  • Black matte epoxy fill adds contrast and stability

  • Oil-based finish + micro-ceramic topcoat for durable, low-sheen protection

  • Size to your wall: standard sizes or custom up to 48″×96″

  • Built to order in Texas • 1-year craftsmanship warranty
column5: Home & Garden > Decor > Artwork > Posters, Prints, & Visual Artwork > Visual Artwork

column3:
Overview
Endgrain oak rounds are arranged in a flowing “drift” pattern, revealing ray-fleck, ring geometry, and subtle color shifts. Natural checks and gaps are consolidated with a black matte epoxy, then the surface is hand-finished in an oil-based system sealed with a micro-ceramic coating for a durable, low-sheen feel.

Specs

  • Material: solid oak endgrain rounds on a stable backer

  • Fill: black matte epoxy (structural + aesthetic)

  • Finish: oil-based with micro-ceramic topcoat (durable, low sheen)

  • Profile: approx. 1.25–1.5" deep, gallery-clean edge

  • Built to order in Texas; ships in 2–3 weeks
